@node Introduction "Introduction to Easy Assign"

  @{b}@{u}Introduction@{uu}@{ub}

  Easy Assign it's a program for people who make startup scripts for their games. Now using
my program they have to only edit icons @{"tooltypes" LINK Tooltypes} to make assigns for their games or even
programs. 

  What Easy Assign can do :
    - It can make as much as you want assigns to a directory from witch it was launched.
    - It can run other program before running the main one.
@endnode

@node Requirements "Requirements for Easy Assign"

  @{b}@{u}Requirements@{uu}@{ub}

  Easy Assign should run on any Amiga with Kickstart 2.0+. It was written for HD users so it's
good to have one (but not needed). I have tested my program on my A1200 Kickstart 3.0, 6 MB of
RAM and 540 MB HD.
@endnode

@node Installation "Installation on HD"

  @{b}@{u}Installation@{uu}@{ub}

  Installation is very easy. You just have to copy EasyAssign to your command 'C:' directory.
@endnode

@node Using "How to use Easy Assign"

  @{b}@{u}Using@{uu}@{ub}

  To use Easy Assign you have to change program icon type to 'Project' (this can be done by
icon edit tool). Then you have to edit @{"tooltypes" LINK Tooltypes} of program icon.

  To make assigns type:

            ASSIGN1=name1
            ASSIGN2=name2
            ASSIGN3=name3   etc...

  Were "names" are names of devices to assign (without trailing ':'). You can make as many
assigns as you want.

  To run other program before running the main one type:

            RUN=string

  Were "string" is a command string.

  Example:

            ASSIGN1=Disk1
            ASSIGN2=Disk2
            ASSIGN3=Disk3
            ASSIGN4=Disk4
            ASSIGN5=Disk5
            ASSIGN6=SaveDisk
            RUN=Avail FLUSH

  And finally you have to write 'EasyAssign' in default tool field.
@endnode

@node Copyright "Easy Assign Copyright"

  @{b}@{u}Copyright@{uu}@{ub}

  Easy Assign is postcardware.  It means you can freely copy it, give it to
your friends etc.  But if you decide to use it, you have to send a postcard
to the @{"author" link Author}.  You mustn't modify any file or reassemble executables.

  Easy Assign has been tested for a long time and found stable in everyday use.
However the author is not responsible for any loss of data, damages to
software or hardware that may result directly or indirectly from the use of
this program.
@endnode

